-- Centerra Gold Says Workers Begin Strike at Kyrgyz Mine, Suspending Output
-- B y   S t e v e n   F r a n k
-- 2010-10-01T11:09:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/centerra-gold-says-workers-begin-strike-at-kyrgyz-mine-suspending-output.html
Centerra Gold Inc. said unionized
workers at its Kumtor mine in the Kyrgyz Republic began a strike
today, suspending production at the facility. The company is in
discussions with the union to resolve the strike, Centerra said
today in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Steven Frank in Toronto at 
